So if you were to look at
my recently-played games,

00:10:42.224 --> 00:10:44.300
you would see that I'm
playing "Brave Frontier"

00:10:44.300 --> 00:10:47.024
and "Robot Unicorn Attack
2"-- fantastic titles--

00:10:47.024 --> 00:10:49.440
and you tap through those,
they would take you to the Play

00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:52.960
Store, and convert those
people into new users.

00:10:52.960 --> 00:10:55.722
Also in the Play Games app,
we have specialized top charts

00:10:55.722 --> 00:10:57.930
that show games that have
integrated with Play Games,

00:10:57.930 --> 00:11:00.140
including a popular
multiplayer category.

00:11:00.140 --> 00:11:03.060
And the ability to search for
those titles within it as well.

00:11:03.060 --> 00:11:04.680
And lastly, we
announced this week

00:11:04.680 --> 00:11:07.090
that we've updated the game
categories in the Google Play

00:11:07.090 --> 00:11:08.934
Store with 18 new genres.

00:11:08.934 --> 00:11:11.350
And that helps people find
games that they love in a genre

00:11:11.350 --> 00:11:14.440
that they care about.

00:11:14.440 --> 00:11:16.250
DAN GALPIN: But
the real question

00:11:16.250 --> 00:11:18.630
is, how do we approach
our stealth gamer?

00:11:18.630 --> 00:11:20.490
They appreciate sign-in
with Cloud Save,

00:11:20.490 --> 00:11:22.740
but we don't really have
anything for social discovery

00:11:22.740 --> 00:11:25.940
for them, until now.

00:11:25.940 --> 00:11:29.580
So we're adding Game Gifts to
the list of Google Play Games

00:11:29.580 --> 00:11:30.680
services.

00:11:30.680 --> 00:11:33.190
Game Gifts is a service that
enables users to both send

00:11:33.190 --> 00:11:35.155
and ask each for in-game items.

00:11:35.155 --> 00:11:37.440
I'm going to go
through the basic flow.

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:41.460
So we start off by actually
giving UI in the game

00:11:41.460 --> 00:11:44.610
to actually send an extra life,
and of course, extra lives

00:11:44.610 --> 00:11:47.114
look like mushrooms.

00:11:47.114 --> 00:11:48.655
And just to show
we're honest, here's

00:11:48.655 --> 00:11:50.870
the code you would actually
execute to do this.

00:11:50.870 --> 00:11:53.710
All you do is request a
send intent with type gift.

00:11:53.710 --> 00:11:55.440
Inside of the intent,
you can include

00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:57.650
a binary payload,
whatever you want,

00:11:57.650 --> 00:12:01.571
the lifetime of the
gift in days, an icon,

00:12:01.571 --> 00:12:02.320
and a description.

00:12:04.960 --> 00:12:07.090
Back to our flow.

00:12:07.090 --> 00:12:08.780
Google Play Games
then displays the UI

00:12:08.780 --> 00:12:10.270
to select the player to gift.

00:12:10.270 --> 00:12:14.420
I recommend following this
example, and gifting me.

00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:16.950
The request heads into
our cloud and notification

00:12:16.950 --> 00:12:19.370
is posted to receiver's device.

00:12:19.370 --> 00:12:21.535
They actually get this
aggregate view of anyone

00:12:21.535 --> 00:12:23.234
who sent them gifts,
whether or not

00:12:23.234 --> 00:12:24.650
they're actually
in their circles,

00:12:24.650 --> 00:12:27.350
and then from there they can
actually accept the gift.

00:12:27.350 --> 00:12:29.080
Now if they don't
yet have the game,

00:12:29.080 --> 00:12:31.000
then they're brought
to Google Play,

00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:33.230
and Google Play will go
and install the game.

00:12:33.230 --> 00:12:36.170
And then they can
actually accept the gift,

00:12:36.170 --> 00:12:38.166
and this is what it looks like.

00:12:38.166 --> 00:12:40.040
You actually end up
getting incoming requests

00:12:40.040 --> 00:12:41.360
in an unconnected bundle.

00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:44.000
And our game helper sample also
provides a get request method

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:46.540
to fetch these requests,
as in this example.

00:12:46.540 --> 00:12:48.110
We also register a
request listener,

00:12:48.110 --> 00:12:50.690
which means if the game
is actually running,

00:12:50.690 --> 00:12:53.720
you can actually just get these
game requests within the game,

00:12:53.720 --> 00:12:56.370
you don't have to direct
people into this flow.

00:12:56.370 --> 00:12:58.600
And you can accept them,
just by handling requests.

00:12:58.600 --> 00:13:00.100
And the game should
probably display

00:13:00.100 --> 00:13:02.330
some UX to allow the
gifts to be accepted,

00:13:02.330 --> 00:13:04.810
since Play Games does not.

00:13:04.810 --> 00:13:07.760
And here's how you actually
handle the callback

00:13:07.760 --> 00:13:09.160
once you've accepted
the request.

00:13:09.160 --> 00:13:11.470
Note that the response doesn't
actually contain details

00:13:11.470 --> 00:13:13.815
about the request, which
is why I cashed the request

00:13:13.815 --> 00:13:15.020
objects to begin with.

00:13:15.020 --> 00:13:17.720
And yes, you use empty blocks
is where you'd actually

00:13:17.720 --> 00:13:20.910
handle the requests
within your game.

00:13:20.910 --> 00:13:22.400
OK, so back to our flow.

00:13:22.400 --> 00:13:25.830
Now we've accepted the request
and we get an extra life!

00:13:25.830 --> 00:13:28.460
You can also actually
show the inbox request

00:13:28.460 --> 00:13:30.740
inside of your game.

00:13:30.740 --> 00:13:32.635
So we talked a little
bit about gifting,

00:13:32.635 --> 00:13:34.260
and that was a pretty
complicated flow,

00:13:34.260 --> 00:13:36.670
but I actually
left something out.

00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:39.280
So after you've actually
accepted the gift,

00:13:39.280 --> 00:13:43.540
we allow you to get the
results of the transaction.

00:13:43.540 --> 00:13:45.395
And this allows you to
do things like trades

00:13:45.395 --> 00:13:46.752
within our gifting system.

00:13:46.752 --> 00:13:47.710
So this is pretty cool.

00:13:47.710 --> 00:13:49.168
Instead of just
accepting the life,

00:13:49.168 --> 00:13:51.415
you can actually prompt
the user and say, hey,

00:13:51.415 --> 00:13:53.790
do you want to trade
this for some other item?

00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:55.420
And sure.

00:13:55.420 --> 00:13:58.000
And so if the user
accepts that trade,

00:13:58.000 --> 00:13:59.460
it'll send a message
back, and you

00:13:59.460 --> 00:14:01.150
can find out that
the item was traded.

00:14:01.150 --> 00:14:03.280
And this way you can actually
set up complex flows.

00:14:03.280 --> 00:14:06.230
You could say, hey, no, I'm
not going to accept this item,

00:14:06.230 --> 00:14:07.390
but here is my offer.

00:14:07.390 --> 00:14:10.270
And you could actually have a
complex negotiation scenario

00:14:10.270 --> 00:14:15.150
going on between players,
all hosted by Play Games.

00:14:15.150 --> 00:14:18.140
So now you've made a game
that all three archetypes play

00:14:18.140 --> 00:14:20.270
and discover using Play
Games, which is awesome.

00:14:20.270 --> 00:14:23.360
But the next question is, how
