00:14:25.739 --> 00:14:27.280
GREG HARTRELL: So
to precisely answer

00:14:27.280 --> 00:14:28.380
the question of how
you're successful,

00:14:28.380 --> 00:14:31.160
you need to think about who
are these different personas?

00:14:31.160 --> 00:14:33.714
And how can I see that
I'm engaging them,

00:14:33.714 --> 00:14:35.880
and that Play Games is
actually making a difference?

00:14:35.880 --> 00:14:39.510
So this week, we're launching
a new update to the Google Play

00:14:39.510 --> 00:14:42.610
developer console, and we
call it Enhanced Play Games

00:14:42.610 --> 00:14:43.940
Statistics.

00:14:43.940 --> 00:14:45.650
What's fascinating
about the statistics

00:14:45.650 --> 00:14:49.500
for Play Games adopters is,
it allows you near-zero effort

00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:52.141
analytics by virtue of
incorporating Google Play

00:14:52.141 --> 00:14:52.640
Games.

00:14:52.640 --> 00:14:56.580
It comes in the form of a daily
dashboard that you can view,

00:14:56.580 --> 00:14:59.614
providing you player and
engagement analytics,

00:14:59.614 --> 00:15:01.780
for you to better measure
the success of your titles

00:15:01.780 --> 00:15:04.450
between updates and for the
types of content you added.

00:15:04.450 --> 00:15:07.200
So let's take a closer look.

00:15:07.200 --> 00:15:08.780
OK, that's too close.

00:15:08.780 --> 00:15:09.510
Alright.

00:15:09.510 --> 00:15:13.480
So for the best game ever, you
need the best ever dashboard.

00:15:13.480 --> 00:15:15.690
And so we'll do a
quick tour here.

00:15:15.690 --> 00:15:17.710
What I can see in
this best game ever

00:15:17.710 --> 00:15:21.500
is a quick, at-a-glance, metrics
of recent days of new players,

00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:23.030
and active players--
ones that I've

00:15:23.030 --> 00:15:24.640
converted into coming back.

00:15:24.640 --> 00:15:28.230
I can also get a quick glance
at my retention data, which

00:15:28.230 --> 00:15:31.230
gives me a quick glance
at several days of running

00:15:31.230 --> 00:15:32.700
day two averages.

00:15:32.700 --> 00:15:35.020
And then I can look at
my engagement statistics,

00:15:35.020 --> 00:15:37.930
particularly for achievements
and leaderboards, achievements

00:15:37.930 --> 00:15:40.860
both in terms of what's earning,
and the meantime to unlock,

00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:44.430
and also leaderboard activity
in terms of scores posted.

00:15:44.430 --> 00:15:47.470
The dashboard also
provides delta metrics,

00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:50.190
so I can at a glance
quickly determine

00:15:50.190 --> 00:15:52.390
whether I'm increasing
or decreasing

00:15:52.390 --> 00:15:53.610
engagement with my players.

00:15:53.610 --> 00:15:55.830
And I can use this in
a variety of scenarios,

00:15:55.830 --> 00:15:57.394
depending on how
I manage my game.

00:15:57.394 --> 00:15:58.810
So let's take a
look at the player

00:15:58.810 --> 00:16:01.040
stats when you dive deep.

00:16:01.040 --> 00:16:03.070
This gives you your
trend lines for players

00:16:03.070 --> 00:16:04.630
who sign in to play games.

00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:09.370
And your rubric is, I have
new players who are coming in,

00:16:09.370 --> 00:16:11.250
I can see which ones
are becoming active,

00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:13.210
and I can see how
I'm retaining them.

00:16:13.210 --> 00:16:15.090
So the quintessential
scenario here

00:16:15.090 --> 00:16:18.010
is, you've just updated your
title, your goal of that title

00:16:18.010 --> 00:16:23.060
was to improve-- or rather
reactivate-- all of your users,

00:16:23.060 --> 00:16:24.930
or a large swath
of them, and you

00:16:24.930 --> 00:16:27.070
could see your trend lines
and your active players

00:16:27.070 --> 00:16:29.780
to validate whether
you've accomplished that.

00:16:29.780 --> 00:16:32.310
A more interesting scenario
is through player retention.

00:16:32.310 --> 00:16:37.100
So this dashboard gives you
the ever-important new player

00:16:37.100 --> 00:16:38.300
return rate.

00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:40.179
And what new player
return rate is,

00:16:40.179 --> 00:16:42.720
here's the number of people who
started playing on this date,

00:16:42.720 --> 00:16:46.960
and 1, 2, 7, and 30 days
later they came back.

00:16:46.960 --> 00:16:50.460
And many of you use
this as a key metric

00:16:50.460 --> 00:16:53.560
for deciding whether the
early game of your title

00:16:53.560 --> 00:16:56.220
is compelling or is successful.

00:16:56.220 --> 00:16:57.950
And so the use
case here, you just

00:16:57.950 --> 00:17:01.890
updated your title to compress
let's say your tutorial flow,

00:17:01.890 --> 00:17:03.740
and maybe enhance
some of the things

00:17:03.740 --> 00:17:06.530
that you're showing within
the first 24-hour period,

00:17:06.530 --> 00:17:08.920
with the goal of increasing
day two retention.

00:17:08.920 --> 00:17:10.980
And so what you would
see here on let's say

00:17:10.980 --> 00:17:15.720
March 8th, going from March 7th,
is you accomplished that goal.

00:17:15.720 --> 00:17:18.690
You saw a bump in day two
retention as a result,

00:17:18.690 --> 00:17:21.400
and you know that your tutorial
flow changes were fixed.

00:17:21.400 --> 00:17:24.319
And again, this data is all
based on Play Games signed-in

00:17:24.319 --> 00:17:25.280
users.

00:17:25.280 --> 00:17:28.520
Gives you all of this
data on a daily basis.

00:17:28.520 --> 00:17:31.150
Let's switch over to the
engagement analytics.

00:17:31.150 --> 00:17:33.180
So this focuses on
achievements in leaderboards.

00:17:33.180 --> 00:17:35.010
And so if you think
about the archetypes

00:17:35.010 --> 00:17:38.010
that we talked about earlier,
such as the achiever,

00:17:38.010 --> 00:17:40.790
and the competitor,
let's say that you added

00:17:40.790 --> 00:17:43.270
an achievement towards
the end of your game

00:17:43.270 --> 00:17:46.360
and you can kind of see that
this is the one that helps them

00:17:46.360 --> 00:17:48.310
get to that very special
level that I know

00:17:48.310 --> 00:17:49.759
has a ton of content.

00:17:49.759 --> 00:17:51.800
I can see if my achiever's
actually chasing that,

00:17:51.800 --> 00:17:53.230
or whether they're
finding things

00:17:53.230 --> 00:17:55.740
that are impeding
them along the way.

00:17:55.740 --> 00:17:58.560
Or if the competitor is, let's
say you added a new tournament

00:17:58.560 --> 00:18:00.960
mode to your game, you
can use the leaderboard

00:18:00.960 --> 00:18:03.990
that's backing that tournament
to see the number of scores

00:18:03.990 --> 00:18:06.472
that are posted, and the
velocity of people engaging

00:18:06.472 --> 00:18:08.680
in that, to decide whether
your tournament system was

00:18:08.680 --> 00:18:09.790
successful.

00:18:09.790 --> 00:18:12.500
So we're very excited to
launch this for all Play Games

00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:13.000
adopters.

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:15.300
It's available in the Google
Play Developer Console

00:18:15.300 --> 00:18:16.209
this week.

00:18:16.209 --> 00:18:18.000
We can't wait to see
what you do to improve

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:19.940
the metrics of your titles.

00:18:19.940 --> 00:18:22.280
OK, so that brings us
to the end of our talk.

00:18:22.280 --> 00:18:25.960
We're going to do a quick recap,
to see what we learned today.

00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:28.230
First is, we learned
that Play Games is

00:18:28.230 --> 00:18:32.040
a highly concentrated network of
people who love playing games.

00:18:32.040 --> 00:18:34.290
We know that they play
longer, they play more often,

00:18:34.290 --> 00:18:36.990
and they're more likely
to monetize in your title.

00:18:36.990 --> 00:18:40.300
We learned about three personas,
the achiever, the competitor,

00:18:40.300 --> 00:18:41.780
and this stealth gamer.

00:18:41.780 --> 00:18:44.290
For the competitor, we have
direct social experiences,

00:18:44.290 --> 00:18:46.650
and for the achiever we
have progression mechanics.

00:18:46.650 --> 00:18:48.600
And for the stealth
gamer, who is

00:18:48.600 --> 00:18:50.807
interested in passive
social experiences,

00:18:50.807 --> 00:18:52.890
we've launched Game Gifts,
which we're rolling out

00:18:52.890 --> 00:18:56.340
with the next Play services
update over the next week.

00:18:56.340 --> 00:18:58.970
We learned a number of
growth hacking techniques,

00:18:58.970 --> 00:19:03.300
using Google Play Store
and Google Play Games,

00:19:03.300 --> 00:19:06.640
such as the top charts
in the Games app

00:19:06.640 --> 00:19:08.610
and seeing what
people are playing.

00:19:08.610 --> 00:19:10.890
And through multiplayer
notifications,

00:19:10.890 --> 00:19:12.560
you can convert new
users who have not

00:19:12.560 --> 00:19:15.740
played the game by virtue
of social discovery.

00:19:15.740 --> 00:19:17.420
And last, but
certainly not least,

00:19:17.420 --> 00:19:19.920
we give you tools to measure
your success through the Google

00:19:19.920 --> 00:19:22.490
Play Developer Console with
enhanced Play Games statistics

00:19:22.490 --> 00:19:24.662
for all of your signed-in users.

